# VS Code Productivity Guide for DevOps Engineers (Beginner to Professional)

## 1. Why Learn VS Code Shortcuts?

As a DevOps Engineer, you will spend most of your time working with:

* YAML files (Kubernetes, GitHub Actions, Azure DevOps)
* Terraform files
* Shell Scripts
* Dockerfiles
* Python scripts
* Configuration files
* Logs and troubleshooting

Using shortcuts can save 1-2 hours every day.

---

# 2. Most Important Shortcuts (Learn First)

## File Navigation

| Action             | Windows/Linux    | Mac             |
| ------------------ | ---------------- | --------------- |
| Quick Open File    | Ctrl + P         | Cmd + P         |
| New File           | Ctrl + N         | Cmd + N         |
| Save File          | Ctrl + S         | Cmd + S         |
| Close File         | Ctrl + W         | Cmd + W         |
| Reopen Closed File | Ctrl + Shift + T | Cmd + Shift + T |

### Example

Instead of manually opening:

```text
terraform/main.tf
```

Press:

```text
Ctrl + P
```

Type:

```text
main.tf
```

Press Enter.

---

# 3. Search Like a Pro

## Search in Current File

```text
Ctrl + F
```

## Replace in Current File

```text
Ctrl + H
```

## Search Entire Project

```text
Ctrl + Shift + F
```

## Replace Entire Project

```text
Ctrl + Shift + H
```

### Real DevOps Example

Need to replace:

```yaml
image: nginx:1.23
```

with

```yaml
image: nginx:1.24
```

across 50 Kubernetes files.

Use:

```text
Ctrl + Shift + H
```

instead of editing one by one.

---

# 4. Multi-Cursor Editing (Super Productivity Booster)

## Add Multiple Cursors

```text
Alt + Click
```

## Select Next Matching Word

```text
Ctrl + D
```

## Select All Matching Words

```text
Ctrl + Shift + L
```

### Example

Change:

```yaml
replicas: 2
```

to

```yaml
replicas: 3
```

in multiple places simultaneously.

