# 16. Top 10 Shortcuts to Memorize First

1. Ctrl + P → Open File
2. Ctrl + Shift + P → Command Palette
3. Ctrl + Shift + F → Search Project
4. Ctrl + D → Multi Select
5. Shift + Alt + F → Format Code
6. Ctrl + ` → Terminal
7. Ctrl + / → Comment
8. F2 → Rename
9. F12 → Go To Definition
10. Ctrl + Shift + G → Git

Master these 10 shortcuts first. They will give you 80% of the productivity improvement.

